Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
resetMultiColorsHier(25.10)                        resetMultiColorsHier(25.10)

Name
       resetMultiColorsHier - Resets the color Id for all or the specified hi-
       erarchical instances

Syntax
       resetMultiColorsHier

       [-help]

       [<colorID> [<hInstName>]]

       Resets the color Id for all or the specified hierarchical instances.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each resetMultiColorsHier parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man resetMultiColorsHier.

       <colorID>
              Specifies  the  color  Id to which all hierarchical instances or
              the specified hierarchical instance will be reset.

              The valid values of color Id are from 0 to 29. The  color  value
              for  the  color  id is the same as specified in the Module Color
              Preference form (accessed by clicking Floorplan - Edit Floorplan
              - Color Module).

              Default: If no color Id and no instance name is  specified,  all
              hierarchical  instances  are displayed with the color id 0. This
              is the same behavior as the Reset button  on  the  Module  Color
              Preferences form.

       <hInstName>
              Specifies  the name of hierarchical instance that should be dis-
              played in the color corresponding to the specified color Id.

              Default: If no instance is specified, the color Id for all hier-
              archical instances is reset.

Example
              * The following command resets the color Id for all hierarchical
                instances and their descendants to 3:

                resetMultiColorsHier 3

              * The following command resets the color Id for the hierarchical
                instance <DTMF_INST> and all its descendants to the  color  id
                3:

                resetMultiColorsHier 3 DTMF_INST

Related Information
              * saveHInstColor

              * setMultiColorsHier

              * setSelHInstColor

              * Floorplan Menu chapter in the Menu Reference

                * Color Module

